</h3><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-24_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health and Safety Executive (HSE) statistics highlight that prompt first aid responses, such as applying for the recovery position, can significantly improve emergency outcomes. For instance, in scenarios where individuals suffer from seizures or are incapacitated due to intoxication or injury, the recovery position can prevent the airway from becoming obstructed by the tongue or vomit, thereby reducing the risk of asphyxiation.
